                                 Ripper Reply@1
                                 ============
@4
Well!   People that are not on the Ripper Mailing list,  Might be quite  taken
aback  at the original Mail from Barry.  As were quite a few that are  on  the
list,   However I am sure it was written in a moment of "dire" Frustration and
annoyance  that  once  AGAIN we have to "Badger" "Bully"  and  "Threaten"  the
readers to get them to submit articles for inclusion in the Magazine.

Strange!  that after this posting, We received several articles, just the next
day!   Proof  @1(if  any  was required)@4  That the ability  is  there,   But  the
willingness lacking.

The letter from Barry was as@2 "A Kick up the Backside"@4 Fortunately it worked  as
intended and generated the required response. On the subject of "Jumping Ship"
Well  its  true the our editor has been using "Linux" running on a  PC  ...For
quite  some  time now.  However is any further proof was required  as  to  his
loyalties He continues to Produce the Ripper @1(an Amiga based Magazine)@4. Lets
face it do Amiga Inc use the Outdated Amiga1200 for all their office staff? Do
the printed Magazines use Amiga's and Pagestream for their presentation ,  NO!



People must use the most applicable tools at hand to do the job to the best of
their  ability.  Barry compiles the Web version of the Ripper,  A  PC  running
"Linux" is far better equipped to handle this task than any Amiga.

As  James  says @1 "Support our community" ...@4I don't think  We @2 (at  Dreamscape
Productions)@4 need to Prove OUR loyalty Rather that the readers out there who
do not contribute to the Magazine#8 NEED@4 to prove their loyalty 
@6
                            Support us or we Die!
@1
                             <@3 Ian Fyvie Co-Ed@1 >

